definition.value: A UDP-sugar having D-galactose as the sugar component.
A alpha,beta-unsaturated monocarboxylic acid that is ethene substituted by a carboxy group.

A member of the class of indolones that is 1,3-dihydro-2H-indol-2-one substituted by a 3-oxo-1,3-dihydro-2H-indol-2-ylidene group at position 3. It is the active component of Dang Gui Long Hui Wan, which has been used in traditional Chinese medicine to treat inflammatory diseases and chronic myeloid leukemia.
An alkenyl thiohydroximate-O-sulfate with a terminal double bond
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA(4-) with fatty acid chain of undefined length containing a oxo group at position 3 and a methyl substituent at the (omega-1) position.
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA(4-) with fatty acid chain of undefined length containing a hydroxy group at position 3R and a methyl substituent at the (omega-1) position.
A methyl-branched fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 14-methylpentadecanoic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
This compound described both aliphatic and aromatic glucosinolates
A hydroxynitrile that is butanenitrile substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.
An acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbon having the general formula CnH2n+2, and therefore consisting entirely of hydrogen atoms and saturated carbon atoms.
An isothiocyanate that is 1-isothiocyanatopropane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.
